        <para>If the current flowing in the conductor were plotted as a function of the angle between the plane of the conductor and the magnetic field, then the current would vary as shown in <link target-id="fig:ac"/>. The current alternates about zero and is known as an <emphasis effect="italics">alternating current</emphasis> (abbreviated AC).</para>
        <figure id="fig:ac">
          <type>figure</type>
