          </pspicture>
          <para>Instead of rotating the loops through a magnetic field to create electricity, a current is sent through the wires, creating electromagnets. The outer magnets will then repel the electromagnets and rotate the shaft as an electric motor. If the current is AC, the two slip rings are required to create an AC motor. An AC motor is shown in <link target-id="fig:ACmotor"/></para>
          <figure id="fig:ACmotor">
            <type>figure</type>
            <pspicture>
              <code>
                (-0.2,-3.2)(9,3.2)
